  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 47a621783cb453147b01764dde5ed130, type: 3}
  m_Name: R1_1_CollectWoodDialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCDialogue
  dialogueLines:
  - So... William sent you back here.
  - That old guardian always did prefer dramatic warnings.
  - Still, he is right...
  - If the magival world is to recover, you must learn the craft of the Moonwardens.
  - Magic is not restored through force, dear.
  - It is restored through patience, understanding... and practice.
  - We'll begin with something simple. A Moondrop Tonic.
  - Most Moonwarden recipes are written as sequences of steps. Each action matters,
    and the order matters just as much.
  - Before any potion can be brewed, the fire under the cauldron must be lit.
  - Collect two pieces of wood, and we'll begin.
  - Every potion begins with fire.
  - Gather two pieces of wood so we can light the cauldron.
  - Good. A steady flame is the foundation of every brew.
